                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/812.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-21T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 19, 8 p.m., which I read to Langley, Assistant Under Secretary of
                    State for Foreign Affairs. He replied that Belgian Minister in London had
                    already informally approached Foreign Office in the matter, and had been
                    answered in almost precisely the same language used in your proposed reply to
                    the Belgian Minister at Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
